{"title": "Philosophy and Civilization in the Middle Ages", "description": "The purpose of the study as here presented is to approach the Middle Ages from a new point of view, by showing how the thought of the period, metaphysics included, is intimately connected with the whole round of Western civilization to which it belongs. My work represents simply an attempt to open the way; it makes no pretense to exhaustive treatment of any of the innumerable problems involved in so vast a subject. - Summary by Preface", "duration": 29920, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18522", "name": "Maurice de Wulf"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/philosophycivilizationmiddleages_2602_librivox/philosophymiddleages_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1922", "genres": ["Middle Ages/Middle History", "Medieval"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "InTheDesert"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Devorah Allen"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [18946], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philosophycivilizationmiddleages_2602_librivox/philosophycivilization_01_dewulf_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1610}, {"section": 2, "title": "Survey of Civilization in the Twelfth Century", "readers": [20067], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philosophycivilizationmiddleages_2602_librivox/philosophycivilization_02_dewulf_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2050}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Civilization as Reflected in Philosophy Part 1", "readers": [11169], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philosophycivilizationmiddleages_2602_librivox/philosophycivilization_03_dewulf_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1369}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Civilization as Reflected in Philosophy Part 2", "readers": [925], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/philosophycivilizationmiddleages_2602_librivox/philosophycivilization_04_dewulf_64kb.mp3", "duration"